## Walkthrough

Grammar Coach v3.0 introduces comprehensive grammar analysis for Japanese worksheets with new backend services for slot detection, distribution metrics, validity assessment, diagnostics, and cloze analysis. Frontend adds unified Language Coach UI with distribution visualization, diagnostic suggestions, and pattern overview. Database schema expands with slot definitions, vocabulary tags, grammar rules, and mappings. Seed data drives particle-to-slot correlations and aspect/category definitions.

## Changes

| Cohort / File(s) | Summary |
|---|---|
| **Documentation** <br> `GRAMMAR_COACH_*.md`, `LANGUAGE_COACH_AUDIT_stage_0.md` | Comprehensive multi-phase documentation: algorithm specification, audit report, execution guide, gap analysis, pre-implementation planning, v3 audit, and walkthrough for v3.0 rollout and testing |
| **Backend Entities** <br> `src/main/java/.../entity/{SlotDefinition, VocabTag, VocabTagMapping, GrammarRule, RuleSuggestion}.java`, `...Vocab.java` | New JPA entities for slot definitions, vocabulary semantic tags with many-to-many mapping, grammar rules with rule types (OVERUSE/MISSING/REQUIRES), and rule suggestions; Vocab extended with partOfSpeech, category, and aspects fields |
| **Backend Core Services** <br> `src/main/java/.../service/{SlotDetectionService, DistributionAnalysisService, ValidityCalculationService, DiagnosticGeneratorService, ClozeAnalysisService}.java` | New analysis services: detect grammatical slots from particles; compute word distribution metrics and category coverage; assess worksheet validity; generate diagnostics with severity/suggestions; analyze cloze blanks and suggest answers |
| **Backend Infrastructure Services** <br> `src/main/java/.../service/{SlotSeederService, GrammarRuleService, VocabTagService, WorksheetScannerService}.java`, `SudachiTokenizerService.java` | Seeding, CRUD, and utility services: load slot definitions from JSON; manage grammar rules and suggestions; manage vocab tags; extract Japanese text from worksheet JSON by item type; tokenize with POS via SudachiTokenizerService.tokenizeWithPos |
| **Backend Orchestration** <br> `src/main/java/.../service/GrammarAnalysisService.java` | Refactored as v3.0 orchestrator: chains SlotDetectionService, DistributionAnalysisService, ValidityCalculationService, DiagnosticGeneratorService, ClozeAnalysisService; provides analyzeV3 (new endpoint) and analyze (v2.0 backward-compatible wrapper) |

| **Backend DTOs** <br> `src/main/java/.../dto/{GrammarCoachResult, GrammarAnalysisResult, LessonScope, ExtractedSegment, SlotAssignment}.java` | New data transfer objects: GrammarCoachResult (nested meta/distribution/diagnostics/slotAnalysis/score); GrammarAnalysisResult (POS counts, rule violations); LessonScope (single/range lesson selection); ExtractedSegment and SlotAssignment for location/slot tracking |

    /**

     */
    @Transactional
    public GrammarRule updateRule(Long id, String name, GrammarRule.RuleType ruleType, String suggestionText,
            String targetWord, Integer threshold, Integer priority, Boolean enabled) {
        var rule = ruleRepository.findById(id)
                .orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException("Rule not found: " + id));

        rule.setName(name);
        rule.setRuleType(ruleType);
        rule.setSuggestionText(suggestionText);
        rule.setTargetWord(targetWord);
        rule.setThreshold(threshold);
        if (priority != null)
            rule.setPriority(priority);
        if (enabled != null)
            rule.setEnabled(enabled);

        return ruleRepository.save(rule);
    }

```suggestion
    /**
     * Delete a rule and its suggestions.
     */
    @Transactional
    public void deleteRule(Long id) {
        if (!ruleRepository.existsById(id)) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Rule not found: " + id);
        }
        suggestionRepository.deleteByRuleId(id);
        ruleRepository.deleteById(id);
    }

    /**
     * Add a suggestion to a rule.
     */
    @Transactional
    public RuleSuggestion addSuggestion(Long ruleId, String suggestedWord, String context, Integer priority) {
        var rule = ruleRepository.findById(ruleId)
                .orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException("Rule not found: " + ruleId));

        var suggestion = new RuleSuggestion(rule, suggestedWord, priority != null ? priority : 0);
        suggestion.setContext(context);
        return suggestionRepository.save(suggestion);
    }
```
